288
00:17:56,150 --> 00:17:57,180
No need, I can do it myself.

289
00:17:57,180 --> 00:17:57,810
It's okay.

290
00:17:57,840 --> 00:17:58,860
I'm good at doing laundries.

291
00:17:58,860 --> 00:17:59,430
Trust me.

292
00:17:59,430 --> 00:17:59,980
No need.

293
00:17:59,980 --> 00:18:00,460
I can do it.

294
00:18:00,460 --> 00:18:01,010
No.

295
00:18:01,220 --> 00:18:01,990
Give it to me.

296
00:18:08,190 --> 00:18:09,140
Mother, let's eat.

297
00:18:09,140 --> 00:18:09,600
This...

298
00:18:11,380 --> 00:18:12,310
Look at this kid.

299
00:18:48,990 --> 00:18:49,470
Miss.

300
00:18:49,870 --> 00:18:51,260
Our bodies, to every hair and every bit of skin, are given to us by our parents.

301
00:18:51,260 --> 00:18:52,620
How can you give your life up so easily?

302
00:18:52,620 --> 00:18:53,400
I'm not...

303
00:18:53,610 --> 00:18:55,010
I know what you want to do.

304
00:18:55,790 --> 00:18:57,540
Miss, you must be optimistic.

305
00:18:57,830 --> 00:18:58,340
There's no difficulty we can't overcome

306
00:18:58,340 --> 00:18:59,490
in this world.

307
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:00,730
Even if there is,

308
00:19:00,790 --> 00:19:01,520
we may as well

309
00:19:01,550 --> 00:19:02,080
stay near that difficulty for a while.

310
00:19:02,080 --> 00:19:03,610
It's also an option, right?

311
00:19:03,610 --> 00:19:04,740
I wasn't going to...

312
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:05,540
Of course you were.

313
00:19:05,540 --> 00:19:07,220
Why can't you listen to reason?

314
00:19:07,220 --> 00:19:08,590
You're jumping into the river on such a freezing day.

315
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:09,870
If you fail to die,

316
00:19:09,950 --> 00:19:11,410
you'll only be half alive.

317
00:19:11,460 --> 00:19:12,470
Even if you manage to die,

318
00:19:12,470 --> 00:19:12,980
you'll be soaked out of shape

319
00:19:12,980 --> 00:19:14,150
in the river.

320
00:19:14,170 --> 00:19:14,720
It's terrifying.

321
00:19:14,720 --> 00:19:15,520
You know that?

322
00:19:15,850 --> 00:19:17,490
I wasn't trying to commit suicide.

323
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:19,220
My clothes fell into the river.

324
00:19:19,280 --> 00:19:21,020
Don't make unreasonable excuses like that.

325
00:19:21,020 --> 00:19:22,550
I didn't see any clothes...

326
00:19:32,070 --> 00:19:33,000
I'm sorry, Miss.

327
00:19:33,040 --> 00:19:34,040
I misunderstood.

328
00:19:34,130 --> 00:19:35,060
Wait for me here.

329
00:19:58,900 --> 00:19:59,460
Miss.

330
00:20:01,900 --> 00:20:02,700
Your clothes.

331
00:20:05,050 --> 00:20:06,450
Thank you, Young Master.

332
00:20:15,140 --> 00:20:15,940
Young Master.

333
00:20:16,540 --> 00:20:17,700
Where do you live?

334
00:20:18,060 --> 00:20:18,900
Why have I never

335
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:19,830
seen you before?

336
00:20:20,470 --> 00:20:21,600
Do you know Shen Nuo?

337
00:20:24,280 --> 00:20:25,390
We are from the same hometown.

338
00:20:25,390 --> 00:20:27,190
We live in Shisanli Camp for now.

339
00:20:31,420 --> 00:20:31,860
So,

340
00:20:32,420 --> 00:20:33,660
what's your name?

341
00:20:34,190 --> 00:20:35,140
My name is Chang Feng.

342
00:20:35,140 --> 00:20:36,650
Everyone calls me Thirteen.

343
00:20:36,650 --> 00:20:37,910
Just call me Thirteen.

344
00:20:38,960 --> 00:20:39,820
Chang Feng.

345
00:21:28,850 --> 00:21:29,500
Buddy.

346
00:21:29,940 --> 00:21:30,540
Excuse me,

347
00:21:31,100 --> 00:21:32,500
but wasn't there a troupe

348
00:21:32,530 --> 00:21:33,930
performing here before?

349
00:21:33,980 --> 00:21:34,840
Where are they?

350
00:21:36,050 --> 00:21:37,130
Don't get me started.

351
00:21:37,130 --> 00:21:37,840
Those performers

352
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:39,020
are bad people.

353
00:21:39,180 --> 00:21:41,440
They robbed the Song family and ran away.

354
00:21:42,230 --> 00:21:42,990
Really?

355
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:46,730
What a pity.

356
00:21:46,980 --> 00:21:47,860
I loved

357
00:21:47,900 --> 00:21:48,630
their opera.

358
00:21:49,310 --> 00:21:49,900
Do you know

359
00:21:49,900 --> 00:21:50,830
where they went?

360
00:21:51,220 --> 00:21:52,460
How would I know?

361
00:21:52,750 --> 00:21:53,600
If I knew,

362
00:21:53,620 --> 00:21:55,380
I would have gone to the government's office to collect the reward.

363
00:21:55,380 --> 00:21:56,380
Look around here.

364
00:21:56,640 --> 00:21:57,990
Government officials

365
00:21:58,030 --> 00:21:59,020
came to raid here

366
00:21:59,270 --> 00:22:00,460
again and again.

367
00:22:01,280 --> 00:22:02,460
We're totally messed up.

368
00:22:02,460 --> 00:22:03,070
Who would dare to

369
00:22:03,070 --> 00:22:04,790
stay here at the Carters' Inn after this?

370
00:22:04,790 --> 00:22:06,140
There's nothing we can do.

371
00:22:06,140 --> 00:22:08,090
Let me help you.

372
00:22:08,220 --> 00:22:09,040
Where should I put this?

373
00:22:09,040 --> 00:22:10,040
Just put it there.

374
00:22:13,070 --> 00:22:14,000
This wine jar...

375
00:23:27,330 --> 00:23:28,340
He.

376
00:23:28,460 --> 00:23:30,230
Are there nails on your butt

377
00:23:30,390 --> 00:23:31,870
that get you pinned to the bed or what?

378
00:23:31,870 --> 00:23:33,150
It's already this hour.

379
00:23:33,150 --> 00:23:35,010
Why haven't you started cooking?

380
00:23:36,300 --> 00:23:36,860
Ye'er.

381
00:23:37,620 --> 00:23:38,100
Ye'er.

382
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:39,720
Why isn't

383
00:23:40,420 --> 00:23:41,780
she back yet?

384
00:23:43,360 --> 00:23:43,990
Mother.

385
00:23:44,390 --> 00:23:46,680
Why did it take you so long to do the laundry?

386
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:47,910
Your grandma is asking you to make lunch.

387
00:23:47,910 --> 00:23:48,460
Go.

388
00:23:49,130 --> 00:23:49,780
Mother.

389
00:23:50,410 --> 00:23:51,820
I want to go back to my room and have a rest.

390
00:23:51,820 --> 00:23:53,120
I feel freezing.

391
00:23:53,590 --> 00:23:54,380
Freezing?

392
00:23:55,840 --> 00:23:57,040
Why is there no water?

393
00:23:57,750 --> 00:23:59,080
No one went to get water?

394
00:23:59,260 --> 00:24:00,220
Ye'er, go get some water.

395
00:24:00,220 --> 00:24:02,280
Hurry, go get your father some water.

396
00:24:03,020 --> 00:24:04,280
What's wrong with you?

397
00:24:04,550 --> 00:24:06,480
I froze from doing the laundry outside.

398
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:07,080
Come here.

399
00:24:11,300 --> 00:24:12,300
She caught a cold.

400
00:24:12,740 --> 00:24:13,820
No way.

401
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:15,460
She can't be that fragile.

402
00:24:15,850 --> 00:24:16,300
If you feel cold,

403
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:17,430
go to your room and put on some more clothes.

404
00:24:17,430 --> 00:24:18,560
Then start cooking.

405
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:19,360
Go.

406
00:24:26,230 --> 00:24:27,890
I think she has a little fever.

407
00:24:28,460 --> 00:24:30,320
Should we take her to see a doctor?

408
00:24:31,150 --> 00:24:31,940
Stop it.

409
00:24:32,770 --> 00:24:34,260
The money we have

410
00:24:34,650 --> 00:24:37,280
isn't even enough for Jizu's gifting next month.

411
00:24:37,280 --> 00:24:37,910
Besides,

412
00:24:38,540 --> 00:24:40,140
there are so many chores to do at home.

413
00:24:40,140 --> 00:24:40,790
What if the doctor

414
00:24:40,790 --> 00:24:41,720
says she's sick?

415
00:24:42,150 --> 00:24:43,410
Who will do the chores?

416
00:24:44,150 --> 00:24:44,950
You're right.

417
00:24:45,620 --> 00:24:46,900
She'll get through this.

418
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:47,450
Yes.

419
00:25:26,840 --> 00:25:27,640
Young Master.

420
00:25:27,950 --> 00:25:29,080
You're back so soon.

421
00:25:29,100 --> 00:25:30,360
Did you find anything?

422
00:25:33,750 --> 00:25:34,230
Here.

423
00:25:37,420 --> 00:25:38,220
When the troupe ran away,

424
00:25:38,220 --> 00:25:39,460
they left many costumes

425
00:25:39,460 --> 00:25:40,470
behind.

426
00:25:41,140 --> 00:25:42,630
They all smell like this.

427
00:25:43,390 --> 00:25:43,920
Besides,

428
00:25:44,290 --> 00:25:45,020
when I fought

429
00:25:45,030 --> 00:25:46,220
Yu Xiangjin last time,

430
00:25:46,220 --> 00:25:46,860
I accidentally got some

431
00:25:46,860 --> 00:25:48,140
fragrance powder from her sachet.

432
00:25:48,140 --> 00:25:49,470
It also smelt like this.

433
00:25:49,990 --> 00:25:50,850
It smells like

434
00:25:50,990 --> 00:25:52,650
it's made of some kind of herb.

435
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:54,780
If we investigate in this direction,

436
00:25:54,780 --> 00:25:56,040
we may find something.

437
00:26:14,900 --> 00:26:17,170
Ye... Ye'er.

438
00:26:18,160 --> 00:26:18,720
Man'er.

439
00:26:20,950 --> 00:26:22,060
You should probably sit down

440
00:26:22,060 --> 00:26:22,990
and take a break.

441
00:26:23,450 --> 00:26:24,380
I'm almost done.

442
00:26:31,620 --> 00:26:32,990
Put it down, Man'er.

443
00:26:38,550 --> 00:26:40,080
Why is your forehead so hot?

444
00:26:40,460 --> 00:26:41,720
Let's go to the clinic.

445
00:26:42,060 --> 00:26:42,670
No.

446
00:26:42,690 --> 00:26:44,140
I still have a lot of chores to do.

447
00:26:44,140 --> 00:26:46,200
But you have to be alive first, right?

448
00:26:46,470 --> 00:26:47,990
I happen to have something to do at the clinic.

449
00:26:47,990 --> 00:26:48,720
Come with me.

450
00:26:49,180 --> 00:26:49,640
Man'er.

451
00:26:50,690 --> 00:26:51,890
Thirteen, let's go.

452
00:26:52,060 --> 00:26:53,260
Let's go see a doctor.

453
00:26:54,830 --> 00:26:55,990
Thank you, Miss Man'er.

454
00:26:55,990 --> 00:26:57,400
I'm okay now.

455
00:26:57,420 --> 00:26:57,820
Don't.

456
00:26:59,120 --> 00:27:00,700
The one Lian Man'er is taking you to see

457
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:02,430
is a doctor named Wang Youheng.

458
00:27:02,560 --> 00:27:04,220
Wang Youheng collects herbs up the hill a lot.

459
00:27:04,220 --> 00:27:05,570
Maybe he's quite familiar with

460
00:27:05,570 --> 00:27:06,220
the herbs.

461
00:27:06,790 --> 00:27:08,210
Go let him take a look at this.

462
00:27:08,210 --> 00:27:09,610
Miss Man'er, wait for me.

463
00:27:10,530 --> 00:27:11,590
Aren't you coming?

464
00:27:13,740 --> 00:27:14,560
I'm not.

465
00:27:15,340 --> 00:27:17,000
Man'er must still be mad at me.

466
00:27:17,140 --> 00:27:17,580
Go.

467
00:27:18,870 --> 00:27:19,390
Okay.

468
00:27:20,710 --> 00:27:21,450
I'll go.

469
00:27:25,610 --> 00:27:30,570
[Liu's Clinic]

470
00:27:32,900 --> 00:27:33,570
It's a cold.

471
00:27:34,370 --> 00:27:35,780
Let me get the prescription for you.

472
00:27:35,780 --> 00:27:36,410
Youheng.

473
00:27:37,310 --> 00:27:38,570
I don't need medicine.

474
00:27:42,500 --> 00:27:44,680
It's common to have a cold,

475
00:27:45,060 --> 00:27:46,360
but if you don't take it seriously,

476
00:27:46,360 --> 00:27:48,110
the consequences can be serious.

477
00:27:48,110 --> 00:27:48,640
Besides,

478
00:27:48,780 --> 00:27:50,240
you have such a high fever.

479
00:27:50,270 --> 00:27:51,030
It's very likely that

480
00:27:51,030 --> 00:27:52,120
you'll get other diseases out of this.

481
00:27:52,120 --> 00:27:53,320
You have to take it seriously.

482
00:27:53,320 --> 00:27:53,900
I'm okay.

483
00:27:55,630 --> 00:27:58,230
Youheng, please get the prescription for her.

484
00:27:58,820 --> 00:27:59,420
By the way,

485
00:27:59,510 --> 00:28:01,190
the one outside is my friend.

486
00:28:01,220 --> 00:28:02,140
He's name is Thirteen.

487
00:28:02,140 --> 00:28:03,060
He's injured.

488
00:28:03,380 --> 00:28:04,780
Please take a look at him.

489
00:28:04,870 --> 00:28:05,350
Okay.

490
00:28:09,850 --> 00:28:10,650
What's wrong?

491
00:28:10,880 --> 00:28:11,610
I'm injured.

492
00:28:11,950 --> 00:28:12,790
Where?

493
00:28:12,920 --> 00:28:13,360
Here.

494
00:28:14,240 --> 00:28:15,710
Take off your clothes first.

495
00:28:15,710 --> 00:28:17,240
I'll get you some medicine.

496
00:28:18,480 --> 00:28:19,110
Ye'er.

497
00:28:19,700 --> 00:28:21,030
What are you looking at?

498
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:24,550
Look at you.

499
00:28:25,180 --> 00:28:25,900
You're the one

500
00:28:25,900 --> 00:28:27,280
who does the most chores at home.

501
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,120
You are ordered around all the time

502
00:28:28,120 --> 00:28:29,200
like a servant.

503
00:28:30,310 --> 00:28:32,310
You can't suffer in silence like this anymore.

504
00:28:32,310 --> 00:28:33,970
You have to rise against them.

505
00:28:34,640 --> 00:28:35,310
Man'er.

506
00:28:35,790 --> 00:28:38,050
I know you're saying this for my own good.

507
00:28:38,420 --> 00:28:39,700
But look at me.

508
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:41,380
I have no ability

509
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:42,930
to rise against them at all.

510
00:28:44,070 --> 00:28:45,670
Everyone has their own fate.

511
00:28:45,810 --> 00:28:47,030
This must be my fate.

512
00:28:47,050 --> 00:28:48,400
What fate?

513
00:28:49,740 --> 00:28:50,940
If you want,

514
00:28:52,700 --> 00:28:54,430
you can come make money with me.

515
00:28:54,820 --> 00:28:56,720
When you are financially independent,

516
00:28:56,720 --> 00:28:58,320
you'll be able to fight back.

517
00:28:58,380 --> 00:29:00,380
No one will dare to bully you by then.

518
00:29:01,150 --> 00:29:02,480
Financially "indeed"?

519
00:29:04,890 --> 00:29:05,560
Anyway,

520
00:29:05,750 --> 00:29:07,280
I'll always be on your side.

521
00:29:10,690 --> 00:29:12,180
Thank you, Man'er.

522
00:29:20,070 --> 00:29:20,750
Youheng.

523
00:29:21,550 --> 00:29:23,690
Can you tell

524
00:29:23,710 --> 00:29:25,770
what spice this fragrance is made of?

525
00:29:32,780 --> 00:29:34,860
There's more than one kind of spice in it.

526
00:29:34,860 --> 00:29:37,640
It's mainly made of common spices, like

527
00:29:37,810 --> 00:29:39,210
fennel, mugwood,

528
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:41,340
calamus, and lemongrass.

529
00:29:41,860 --> 00:29:42,620
So,

530
00:29:42,660 --> 00:29:43,750
anyone can make

531
00:29:43,770 --> 00:29:44,590
this fragrance, right?

532
00:29:44,590 --> 00:29:45,990
So it's nothing special?

533
00:29:46,100 --> 00:29:46,940
Not really.

534
00:29:47,550 --> 00:29:49,000
There is a herb in it

535
00:29:49,020 --> 00:29:50,020
called moonwort.

536
00:29:50,320 --> 00:29:51,190
This kind of herb

537
00:29:51,190 --> 00:29:52,190
is quite rare.

538
00:29:52,490 --> 00:29:54,060
This kind of herb is mainly used

539
00:29:54,060 --> 00:29:56,540
to expel a kind of insect called Qianjia earwig.

540
00:29:56,540 --> 00:29:58,980
This kind of insect only appears in few areas.

541
00:29:58,980 --> 00:30:00,240
It likes to suck blood.

542
00:30:00,660 --> 00:30:01,500
Once bitten,

543
00:30:01,540 --> 00:30:02,700
people will get rashes all over their bodies,

544
00:30:02,700 --> 00:30:04,000
and they itch intensely.

545
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:04,920
In serious cases,

546
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:06,520
their lives may even be at risk.

547
00:30:06,520 --> 00:30:07,050
So,

548
00:30:07,260 --> 00:30:08,470
only those who're

549
00:30:08,500 --> 00:30:09,500
troubled by this kind of insect

550
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:11,030
use moonwort to repel them.

551
00:30:13,070 --> 00:30:13,900
Moonwort...

552
00:30:14,480 --> 00:30:15,220
Youheng.

553
00:30:15,700 --> 00:30:17,470
Do you know where

554
00:30:17,740 --> 00:30:19,020
this kind of insect often appears?

555
00:30:19,020 --> 00:30:20,350
If you want to find them,

556
00:30:20,620 --> 00:30:21,880
go south down Hua Ridge

557
00:30:21,900 --> 00:30:22,900
for 50 to 60 miles.

558
00:30:22,990 --> 00:30:24,750
There are fields of moonwort there.

559
00:30:24,750 --> 00:30:25,990
Ask those who collect herbs.

560
00:30:25,990 --> 00:30:28,320
Maybe they can give you some information.

561
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:29,650
Okay.

562
00:30:30,590 --> 00:30:31,730
Sorry for the trouble.

563
00:30:31,730 --> 00:30:32,660
You're welcome.

564
00:30:32,670 --> 00:30:33,470
You can go now.

565
00:30:36,020 --> 00:30:37,650
Take this cold remedy twice a day

566
00:30:37,650 --> 00:30:39,380
for three days, and you should be fine.

567
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:41,110
I brought you some extra doses.

568
00:30:41,140 --> 00:30:42,150
This way,

569
00:30:42,190 --> 00:30:43,220
you can take this medicine as soon as possible

570
00:30:43,220 --> 00:30:44,350
if you catch a cold again.

571
00:30:44,350 --> 00:30:46,150
It also has a preventive effect.

572
00:30:46,330 --> 00:30:46,850
Man'er.

573
00:30:47,380 --> 00:30:49,560
This wine is said to be from the Western Regions.

574
00:30:49,560 --> 00:30:50,930
It's called grape fine wine or something.

575
00:30:50,930 --> 00:30:52,190
Take it back and try it.

576
00:30:54,020 --> 00:30:55,220
Grape wine?

577
00:30:56,030 --> 00:30:57,710
There's wine sold here?

578
00:30:58,300 --> 00:30:59,380
We don't have it here.

579
00:30:59,380 --> 00:31:00,130
My father brought this back

580
00:31:00,130 --> 00:31:01,220
from somewhere else

